---
/**
 * context-engineering 0008 · Figure 4 — Module 2 "the trade-off triangle":
 * recall / latency / memory at the corners, build time in the centre; you can't
 * max all three.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0008-embeddings-indexing-and-cost.html.
 * Lives as an .astro component (not inline MDX) because raw inline SVG with
 * kebab-case attributes is unreliable in MDX but is plain HTML in .astro. This
 * figure references no shared arrowhead markers, so it needs no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 220"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A triangle of recall, latency, and memory; tuning toward one corner pulls away from the others, with build time in the centre."
    >
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >You can't max all three — pick your corner</text
        >
        <polygon points="300,40 120,180 480,180" fill="#f1eef2" stroke="#b5179e" stroke-width="1.5"
        ></polygon>
        <circle cx="300" cy="40" r="5" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
            x="300"
            y="32"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">Recall</text
        >
        <circle cx="120" cy="180" r="5" fill="#1f3a5a"></circle><text
            x="110"
            y="198"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#1f3a5a">Latency</text
        >
        <circle cx="480" cy="180" r="5" fill="#9a2417"></circle><text
            x="490"
            y="198"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">Memory</text
        >
        <text
            x="300"
            y="130"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#b5179e">+ build time</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >HNSW &rarr; recall+latency, costs memory · PQ &rarr; memory, costs recall</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Every index is a point inside this triangle. HNSW buys recall and low latency by spending
        memory; PQ buys memory back by spending recall. <b>Metadata filtering</b> sits alongside: <em
            >pre-filter</em
        > scopes the search before ANN (e.g. by tenant or date), which is also a security boundary for
        Lesson 9; <em>post-filter</em> drops results after, and can return too few.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r5">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
